==Release==
{{Main|List of Devil Survivor 2: The Animation episodes}}
The thirteen-episode series premiered on the [[Animeism]] programming block of [[Mainichi Broadcasting System|MBS]] on April 4, 2013 during the 26:05 (02:05 [[Japan Standard Time|JST]]) time slot. This technically resulted in the episodes airing on the days following the ones scheduled.<ref name="MBS Airdate">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141019030531/http://www.mbs.jp/ds2a/|archivedate=October 19, 2014|url=http://www.mbs.jp/ds2a/|title=DEVIL SURVIVOR2 the ANIMATION　番組サイト|deadurl=no|publisher=[[Mainichi Broadcasting System|Mainichi Broadcasting System, Inc.]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=September 10, 2013}}</ref> The anime was later aired on [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]], [[Chubu-Nippon Broadcasting|CBC]] and [[BS-TBS]] with online streaming on the Japanese [[Niconico]] website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ds2a.jp/onair/|title=On Air｜TVアニメ「デビルサバイバー2」公式サイト［DEVIL SURVIVOR2 the ANIMATION］|publisher=[[Pony Canyon]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=September 8, 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922010102/http://ds2a.jp/onair/|archivedate=September 22, 2013|df=}}</ref> The series was acquired by [[Crunchyroll]] for online simulcast streaming with English subtitles in the territories of USA, Canada, UK, Ireland, South Africa, Australia, New Zealand, Netherlands, and Scandinavia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2013/04/03/crunchyroll-to-stream-devil-survivor-2-the-animation|title=Crunchyroll to Stream "''DEVIL SURVIVOR 2 THE ANIMATION''"|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=April 3, 2013|accessdate=January 10, 2014|first=Patrick|last=Macias|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130406014000/http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2013/04/03/crunchyroll-to-stream-devil-survivor-2-the-animation|archivedate=April 6, 2013|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-04-03/crunchyroll-to-stream-devil-survivor-2-tv-anime|title=Crunchyroll to Stream ''Devil Survivor 2'' TV Anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 17, 2013|accessdate=September 8, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130612001452/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-04-03/crunchyroll-to-stream-devil-survivor-2-tv-anime|archivedate=June 12, 2013|df=}}</ref> The [[Anime Network]] and [[Hulu]] later picked up the series for streaming on their online services. The series was also digitally released on the [[Movies & TV (Microsoft service)|Movies & TV]] platform by [[Microsoft]] and the [[PlayStation Store]].<ref name="Official Sentai"/>

On June 19, 2013, [[Pony Canyon]] began releasing the series on [[Blu-ray]] and DVD volumes in Japan—with the first volume including the first episode and a bonus CD featuring the first Original Soundtrack for the series.<ref name="BD Volume 1">{{cite web|url=http://ds2a.jp/products/bd_01.html#vol1|title=''Devil Survivor 2 The Animation'' Volume 1|publisher=[[Pony Canyon]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=November 26, 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130817181541/http://ds2a.jp/products/bd_01.html#vol1|archivedate=August 17, 2013|df=}}</ref> The following volumes each contained two episodes with all but the fifth and sixth volumes containing bonus discs of which included a three volume Drama CD series.  The seventh and final DVD and Blu-ray volume was released on December 18, 2013 while all Limited Edition volumes were distributed with a bonus poster featuring characters from the series.<ref name="BD Volume 7">{{cite web|url=http://ds2a.jp/products/bd_01.html#vol7|title=Products :Blu-ray&DVD Vol.7｜TVアニメ「デビルサバイバー2」公式サイト［DEVIL SURVIVOR2 the ANIMATION］|publisher=[[Pony Canyon]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=November 26, 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130817181541/http://ds2a.jp/products/bd_01.html#vol7|archivedate=August 17, 2013|df=}}</ref> [[Section23 Films#Sentai Filmworks|Sentai Filmworks]] licensed the series for distribution through selected digital outlets and a home video release in North America.<ref name="Official Sentai">{{cite web|url=http://www.sentaifilmworks.com/shows/devil-survivor-2-the-animation|title=''Devil Survivor 2: The Animation'' - Sentai Filmworks|publisher=[[Section23 Films#Sentai Filmworks|Sentai Filmworks]]|accessdate=August 10, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140706205839/http://www.sentaifilmworks.com/shows/devil-survivor-2-the-animation|archivedate=July 6, 2014|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130420064946/http://sentai-filmworks.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=253%3Asentaifilmworkslicensesdevilsurvivor2theanimation&catid=71%3Apress-releases&Itemid=64|archivedate=April 20, 2013|url=http://www.sentai-filmworks.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=253:sentaifilmworkslicensesdevilsurvivor2theanimation&catid=71:press-releases&Itemid=64|title=Sentai Filmworks Licenses ''Devil Survivor 2 The Animation''|deadurl=yes|publisher=[[Section23 Films#Sentai Filmworks|Sentai Filmworks]]|date=April 18, 2013|accessdate=September 11, 2013|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-04-18/sentai-filmworks-adds-devil-survivor-2-the-animation-tv-anime|title=Sentai Filmworks Adds ''Devil Survivor 2 the Animation'' TV Anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 18, 2013|accessdate=September 8, 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022070933/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-04-18/sentai-filmworks-adds-devil-survivor-2-the-animation-tv-anime|archivedate=October 22, 2014|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2013/04/18/sentai-filmworks-licenses-devil-survivor-2-the-animation-series|title=Sentai Filmworks Licenses "''Devil Survivor 2 The Animation''" Series|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=April 18, 2013|accessdate=January 10, 2014|first=Joseph|last=Luster|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217115416/http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2013/04/18/sentai-filmworks-licenses-devil-survivor-2-the-animation-series|archivedate=December 17, 2013|df=}}</ref> The company released the series in its entirety on DVD format on July 1, 2014 with English and Japanese audio options along with English subtitles.<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419025432/http://www.sentaifilmworks.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=313%3Asentai-filmworks-announces-july-2014-release-schedule&catid=71%3Apress-releases&Itemid=64|archivedate=April 19, 2014|url=http://www.sentaifilmworks.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=313:sentai-filmworks-announces-july-2014-release-schedule&catid=71:press-releases&Itemid=64|title=Sentai Filmworks Announces July 2014 Release Schedule|deadurl=yes|publisher=[[Section23 Films#Sentai Filmworks|Sentai Filmworks]]|date=March 25, 2014|accessdate=September 8, 2014|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2014/03/25/sentai-filmworks-announces-july-anime-release-slate|title=Sentai Filmworks Announces July Anime Release Slate|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=March 25, 2014|accessdate=March 27, 2014|first=Scott|last=Green|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140330023909/http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2014/03/25/sentai-filmworks-announces-july-anime-release-slate|archivedate=March 30, 2014|df=}}</ref> Hanabee Entertainment later licensed the series for a home media release in Australia and New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-06-02/hanabee-acquires-devil-survivor-2-the-animation/.75120|title=Hanabee Acquires ''Devil Survivor 2 The Animation''|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 2, 2014|accessdate=August 10, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140919131408/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-06-02/hanabee-acquires-devil-survivor-2-the-animation/.75120|archivedate=September 19, 2014|df=}}</ref> The company released the complete series on a DVD volume on September 3, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hanabee.myshopify.com/collections/everything/products/devil-survivor-2|title=''Devil Survivor 2'' Hanabee Entertainment|publisher=Hanabee Entertainment|accessdate=August 10, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140813031929/https://hanabee.myshopify.com/collections/everything/products/devil-survivor-2|archivedate=August 13, 2014|df=}}</ref> [[MVM Entertainment]] also obtained the distribution rights in the United Kingdom<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-08-02/mvm-confirms-samurai-champloo-blu-ray/.77213|title=MVM Confirms ''Samurai Champloo'' Blu-ray|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 2, 2014|accessdate=August 10, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150915065230/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-08-02/mvm-confirms-samurai-champloo-blu-ray/.77213|archivedate=September 15, 2015|df=}}</ref> and released it on a single DVD set on October 20, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anime-on-line.com/xcart/product.php?productid=25071&cat=2241&page=1|title=''Devil Survivor 2: The Animation'' Complete Collection (tbc) DVD|publisher=Anime-on-Line|accessdate=August 10, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303222221/http://www.anime-on-line.com/xcart/product.php?productid=25071&cat=2241&page=1|archivedate=March 3, 2016|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MVM_UK/status/495228941607915520|title=Twitter / MVM_UK: ''Devil Survivor 2: The Animation'' ...|publisher=[[Twitter]]|language=Japanese|date=August 1, 2014|accessdate=August 10, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305041817/https://twitter.com/MVM_UK/status/495228941607915520|archivedate=March 5, 2016|df=}}</ref> Pony Canyon released the entire series on a Blu-ray box set in Japan on January 30, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.ds2a.jp/archives/572|title=Blu-ray BOX発売決定！ TVアニメ「デビルサバイバー2」NEWS|publisher=[[Pony Canyon]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=October 14, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141226015948/http://blog.ds2a.jp/archives/572|archivedate=December 26, 2014|df=}}</ref> Sentai Filmworks followed their 2014 DVD release with a Blu-ray format release in North America on April 21, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2014-12-18/section23-films-announces-april-slate/.82364|title=Section23 Films Announces April Slate|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 18, 2014|accessdate=December 20, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141219052855/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2014-12-18/section23-films-announces-april-slate/.82364|archivedate=December 19, 2014|df=}}</ref> Hanabee then followed suit with their own Blu-ray release on May 6, 2015.<ref name="Hanabee BD">{{cite web|url=https://hanabee.myshopify.com/collections/everything/products/devil-survivor-2-bluray|title=''Devil Survivor 2'' Hanabee Entertainment|publisher=Hanabee Entertainment|accessdate=March 1, 2015}}</ref>

==Related media==

===Manga adaptation===
A manga adaptation was serialized in [[Square Enix]]'s ''[[Gangan Comics#Monthly GFantasy|Monthly GFantasy]]'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141015001828/http://ds2a.jp/img/common/img_comicalize.png|archivedate=October 15, 2014|url=http://ds2a.jp/img/common/img_comicalize.png|title=Gファンタジー ［DEVIL SURVIVOR2 the ANIMATION］|deadurl=no|publisher=[[Pony Canyon]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=October 15, 2014}}</ref> It is illustrated by Haruto Shiota and written by Makoto Uezu; based on the original ''Devil Survivor 2'' story by Atlus.<ref name="DS2A Manga">{{cite web|url=http://www.ds2a.jp/products/comic_01.html|title=Products :コミック 1巻｜TVアニメ「デビルサバイバー2」公式サイト［DEVIL SURVIVOR2 the ANIMATION］|publisher=[[Pony Canyon]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=August 24, 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304100855/http://www.ds2a.jp/products/comic_01.html|archivedate=March 4, 2016|df=}}</ref> The manga made its debut in the January 2013 issue of ''GFantasy'' which was published in Japan on December 18, 2012.<ref name="GF January 2013">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B00A9MOX84|title=Gファンタジー 2013年 01月号|publisher=[[Amazon.com|Amazon.co.jp]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=October 15, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307085853/http://www.amazon.co.jp/G%E3%83%95%E3%82%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%82%BF%E3%82%B8%E3%83%BC-2013%E5%B9%B4-01%E6%9C%88%E5%8F%B7/dp/B00A9MOX84|archivedate=March 7, 2016|df=}}</ref> It ran for twenty-five chapters and ended in the November 2014 issue which was published on October 18, 2014.<ref name="GF November 2014">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B00NONBR3Y|title=Gファンタジー 2014年 11月号|publisher=[[Amazon.com|Amazon.co.jp]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=October 15, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307213017/http://www.amazon.co.jp/G%E3%83%95%E3%82%A1%E3%83%B3%E3%82%BF%E3%82%B8%E3%83%BC-2014%E5%B9%B4-11%E6%9C%88%E5%8F%B7/dp/B00NONBR3Y|archivedate=March 7, 2016|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141019054153/http://www.square-enix.co.jp/magazine/gfantasy/new/|archivedate=October 19, 2014|url=http://www.square-enix.co.jp/magazine/gfantasy/new/|title=GFantasy Website 最新号紹介 -月刊Gファンタジーオフィシャルサイト|deadurl=no|publisher=[[Square Enix]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=October 19, 2014}}</ref> The chapters have been collected and released into four [[tankōbon]] volumes between March 27, 2013<ref name="Manga Vol 1"/> and December 27, 2014.<ref name="Manga Vol 4"/>

