{{italic title}} [[File:2000. Stamp of Belarus 0374.jpg|thumb|200px|''Partisan Madonna of Minsk'' on a Belarusian postage stamp, 2000]] '''''Partisan Madonna of Minsk''''' ({{lang-be|"Партызанская Мадонна Мінская"}}) is a painting by Belarusian artist [[Mikhail Savitsky]], completed in 1978 and preceded by similar painting, ''Partisan Madonna'' from 1967. The painting is based on the ''[[Sistine Madonna]]'' by [[Raphael Sanzio]]<ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.artmuseum.by/ru/vyst/50-shedevrov-naczionalnogo-xudozhestvennogo-muzeya/m.saviczkij-%C2%ABpartizanskaya-madonna-minskaya%C2%BB|title=М.Савицкий "Партизанская Мадонна Минская"|publisher=Belarusian National Arts Museum| language=Russian| accessdate =10 Dec 2015}}</ref> and reflects the motherhood and milieu of [[Soviet partisans]] during [[World War II]]. The painting is regarded by [[art critic]]s as one of the best Belarusian paintings of the 20th century.<ref>{{cite web | url =http://artbelarus.by/ru/news/247.html|title=10 самых впечатляющих экспонатов|publisher=Artbelarus.by| language=Russian| accessdate =10 Dec 2015}}</ref> ''Partisan Madonna of Minsk'' is housed in the [[Belarusian National Arts Museum]] in [[Minsk]].
